(firstQuint)Effects Oxygen Supplementation Determined Better Exercise Capacity in Eisenmenger Syndrome.

 Patients with Eisenmenger's syndrome were submitted to a submaximal exercise test (six-minute walking test) with and without supplemental oxygen.

 The distance walked during the two tests were compared to assess the impact of oxygen supplementation on the walking distance.

